<div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-04-0673-sn"><p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ manuscript (arbitrarily applied to most documents other than letters) ]">MS</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Virginia, Richmond ]">Vi</span>); in Archibald Blairs? hand and designated by him (A Copy). <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ manuscript (arbitrarily applied to most documents other than letters) ]">MS</abbr> mutilated; missing matter has been supplied from <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Council of the State of Virginia&lt;/i&gt;, ed. H. R. McIlwaine ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Va. Council Jour</span>.</span>, <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">ii</span>, 287. Enclosed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-05-02-0050" class="document">TJs letter to Speaker R. H. Lee, 1 Mch. 1781</a>, q.v., and endorsed: [Go]vernors Letter Stating sundry Matters March 2d: 1781. Referred to the Committee of the Whole House on the State of the Commonwealth.</p>
 <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0653" class="document">TJ to George Gibson</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0654" class="document">Gibson to TJ, both dated 5 Feb. 1781</a>; see also <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-04-02-0671" class="document">Returns of the State Regiments</a>, same date.</p></div>
